description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Locum Consultant Cardiologist post with a special interest in Cardiac Intervention for Medicine and Emergency Care in East Sussex Hospitals Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join a progressive and dynamic cardiology department with supportive colleagues, working together to improve the cardiac health of our diverse local population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic colleague to join our team and work to deliver consultant led, efficient, safe and patient centered best practice in Cardiology Intervention. The successful applicant would be joining a busy, forward-thinking cardiology department which is continuously looking to innovate and improve services. Newer technologies OCT,Lithotripsy and Impella are available to complement traditional Intracoronary Ultrasound Rotablation and IABP . The appointee should hold a CCST and be accredited in Cardiology as well as trained in coronary intervention. They will form part of the primary angioplasty rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a cross site post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will join a team of 11 Consultant Cardiologists, and will be part of the development of a multi-disciplinary team approach to care within the speciality of cardiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would join ESHT at an exciting time, we were one of the most improved trusts in England in 2018 for our patient flow; currently our 4 hour wait performance is one of the best in the local STP. Our readmission rates are below our peer group, and our trust mortality rates are well below both expected figures and also our wider peer group. We are an organization that places much importance and pride on being clinically led, and are working towards our plan to be&lt;strong&gt; #OUTSTANDINGBY2020!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
